[4] France: update
Date: Tue 31 Jan 2012
Source: French Ministry of Agriculture and Fishing [in French, trans. Corr.SB, summ., edited]
http://agriculture.gouv.fr/maladies-animales


Schmallenberg virus has been identified in sheep in 6 departments of the North of France (departments No 52 [Haute Marne], 54 [Meurthe-et-Moselle], 57 [Moselle], 62 [Pas de Calais], 76 [Seine Maritime], and 80 [Somme]).

The presence of SBV has been confirmed in lambs on 16 new farms in northern France, as of 30 Jan 2012. In total, 29 sheep farms have been affected, mainly in the following 10 departments in the north of France: No 02 (Ainse), 14 (Calvados), 52 (Haute-Marne), 54 (Meurthe-et-Moselle), 55 (Meuse), 57 (Moselle), 60 (Oise), 62 (Pas-de-Calais), 76 (Seine-Maritime), and 80 (Somme).

